textbox.text: No, I didn't. It was quite clear when the circle was really light or dark.
textbox_5.text: I based my judgement on both these strategies. I tried to see how related the colors were and how much I would need to add or remove to make them similar. However, for most of the colors that were the same, like some avocado green, light green, or lime green-yellow, I just judged by the shades. How dark or light they are, if one is darker than the other, then they are different.
textbox_7.text: It was a very interesting study. It really had me questioning my color skills and how much I know about different shaped and names for these diverse colors.
